<p>The <b>global digital divide</b> is a term used to describe “great disparities in opportunity to access the <a href="/wiki/Internet" title="Internet">Internet</a> and the information and educational/business opportunities tied to this access … between developed and <a href="/wiki/Developing_countries" title="Developing countries" class="mw-redirect">developing countries</a>”.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Unlike the traditional notion of the "digital divide" between social classes, the "global digital divide" is essentially a geographical division.</p>
